Glanders, Turkey
----------------
Information received on [and dated] 23 Dec 2019 from Dr Nihat Pakdil, Deputy Undersecretary of Ministry, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry, Ankara, Turkey.

Summary:
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 21 Nov 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 4 Dec 2019
Report date: 23 Dec 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 23 Dec 2019
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 8 Nov 2017
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: _Burkholderia mallei_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (3)
Outbreak 1: Buyukada, Adalar, Istanbul
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Nov 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 1375 / 81 / 0 / 81 / 0
Affected population: in 2017, new arrangements in movements of horses to Istanbul province and Adalar district in line with 2018/1301 EC Directive has been brought following the last outbreak. Veterinary health certificate is obligatory in movements of equids between provinces. Additionally, animals to be moved need to have been tested for glanders and to have an identification document. Those who intend to get horses to Adalar district should receive permission from General Directorate of Food and Control (GDFC). Horses in Adalar district have microchips and identification documents. All of them are subjected to screening for glanders during spring and autumn twice a year. The sick horses were illegally brought to Adalar district without having microchips, identification documents and veterinary health certificates. They were detected in the course of screening in autumn. Totally 1375 horses were screened with CFT [complement fixation test]. 63 blood samples were positive and 18 samples were suspicious of glanders. All suspicious horses were also destroyed with the sick horses. All horses in Adalar district were subjected to both serological and mallein tests for glanders. In total, 81 horses illegally brought to Adalar district were destroyed. Entry and exit to Adalar district have been forbidden. All horses in Adalar district will be subjected to a 2nd test for glanders 20 days later. Quarantine, cleaning, and disinfection measures are being applied.

Outbreak 2: Orencik, Mudurnu, Bolu
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Dec 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 48 / 3 / 0 / 3 / 0
Affected population: the cases were detected in the course of screening carried out with the purpose of identification of equids.

Outbreak 3: Samat, Mudurnu, Bolu
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Dec 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 37 / 7 / 0 / 7 / 0
Affected population: The cases were detected in the course of screening carried out with the purpose of identification of equids.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 1460 / 91 / 0 / 91 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 6.23 / 0 / 0 / 6.23
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: illegal movement of animals

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; quarantine; selective killing and disposal; disinfection; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Etlik Veterinary Control Central Research Institute (national laboratory) / Equidae / complement fixation test [CFT] / 4 Dec 2019 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

